      "text": "__The Archive__ is a term we use to refer to a form of [[Performative Commons]] created for the purpose of social deliberation and [[governance]]. \n"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "49214676210247d8",
      "text": "The purpose of the archive is to provide a robust, sustainable framework for the generation, preservation and access to [[free culture]] material related to informing democratic, deliberative and scientific decision making.\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "7d70ca331d00324a",
      "text": "# Technology\nPart of the requirements of the archive is the provision of technology which enforces, motivates, and provides access and governance to the material stored. A database and the internet is not sufficient for this purpose.\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "e50aad65dd918c58",
      "text": "We require automation to lower the costs of the (legal) agreements, and new forms of incentive to facilitate low cost production of cultural content in the face of difficulties securing finance for quality content with a social purpose."
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "a473288cbaa492bc",
      "text": "# Law\nThe archive provides technology and legal tools to facilitate robust management of copyright, [[free culture]], and [[fair dealing]] provisions regarding material that is being edited."
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "e75e3b32c5893b4a",
      "text": "Current legal frameworks provide theoretical protection for the use of copyrighted material for public purpose under [[fair dealing]] and [[fair use]] provisions. In practice members of society are rarely able to make use of such media due to the prohibitive cost in time and money required to defend such use in the courts.\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "2dd49f2dcfd7329a",
      "text": "# Unequal battle\nThe size and wealth of large copyright holders (media companies), in relation to individual researchers, citizen journalists and educators makes this an unequal legal battle given the current state of the law.\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "df76382955e2dd96",
      "text": "# Defence\n"
    },
    {
      "type": "markdown",
      "id": "29d9ecb0273a36a5",
      "text": "[[The Archive]] seeks to address this issue, through the provision of collective legal defence in the case (and likelihood) of an action being brought against [[The Archive]]. As such The Archive will create a defence fund, and secure partnerships and legal advice in order to maximise the chance of winning in court. It is important that The Archive is structured and governed in such a way as to make such a defence robust, and to minimise the liability of members."
    },
